{"name":"Frink","size":"medium","type":"humanoid","tag":"human","alignment":"chaotic good","hitDice":"5","armorName":"leather armor","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":7,"otherArmorDesc":"10","speed":"30","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":true,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"54 (6d8)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"13","dexPoints":"13","conPoints":"12","intPoints":"18","wisPoints":"14","chaPoints":"15","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"0","telepathy":0,"cr":"6","customCr":"1 (200 XP)","customProf":2,"isLegendary":false,"legendariesDescription":"The monster can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The monster regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the monster can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the monster can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The monster can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":false,"mythicDescription":"If the monster's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using {Some Ability}.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the monster's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the monster dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Magical Tinkering","desc":"Frink can pour a potion on a Tiny nonmagical object as an action and give it one of the following magical properties of Frink's choice:\n The object sheds bright light in a 5-foot radius and dim light for an additional 5 feet.\n Whenever tapped by a creature, the object emits a recorded message (no more than 6 seconds long) that can be heard up to 10 feet away.\n The object continuously emits Frink's choice of an odor or a nonverbal sound. The chosen phenomenon is perceivable up to 10 feet away.\n A static visual effect appears on one of the object's surfaces.\nThe chosen property lasts indefinitely. As an action, Frink can touch the object and end the property early. Frink can bestow magic on up to 4 objects."},{"name":"Random Infusement","desc":"Frink has 4 superposition molds, a clay like object that can be turned into a magic item. Frink can pour a potion onto this mold in order to create an infused item. When activating this infusement, roll 1D112. This will determine what magical item the mold will turn into. A mold can be changed into a new infusement during a long rest."},{"name":"Alchemy Jug","desc":"Frink has an Alchemy Jug."},{"name":"The Right Tool for the Job","desc":"With thieves' tools or artisan's tools in hand, Frink can magically create on set of artisan's tools in an unoccupied space within 5 feet of you. This creation requires 1 hour of uninterrupted work."},{"name":"Tool Expertise","desc":"Frink's proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check Frink makes that uses his proficiency with a tool."},{"name":"Experimental Elixir","desc":"Whenever you finish a long rest, Frink can magically produce up to 2 elixers, each in an empty flask Frink touches.\n Any elixir Frink creates with this feature lasts until it is drunk or until the end of Frinks next long rest.\n Frink can create additional experiment elixirs by expending a spell slot of 1st level or higher for each one."},{"name":"Alchemical Savant","desc":"Whenever Frink casts a spell using his alchemist's supplies, Frink gain's a +4 bonus to one roll of the spell. That roll must restore hit points or be a damage roll that deals acid, fire, necrotic, or poison damage."},{"name":"S